PSAVE is a function in GfA Basic that lets the programmer save his program
in a special format that can be loaded but not listed or compiled. If you
have a program that is uncompiled and pasved, Un-Psave will remove a degree
of the protection and allow you to compile it.

Un-Psave is extremely easy to use. Just follow the on-screen dialog boxes
to un-psave your file. Un-Psave will automatically go through the file and
remove the protection.

As we were writing this program, we could almost hear GfA programmers cry
out, "What about my programs?" As stated above, Un-Psave will only remove
a degree of the protection. Although it can be listed, it is partially
scrambled because GFA removes the variables when psaving. The compiled copy
will remain intact.

Please note that when Un-Psave is working it changes the actual file. That
means if it is a "Read-Only" file it will not work. It also means if you
wish to retain a copy of the psaved file, make a backup. We haven't tried
re-psaving it, although it should work without any problem.

